cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes an end-to-end deep learning architecture for word-level visual speech recognition, which involves processing video data. This makes it highly likely to belong to the computer vision sub-category.
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with speech recognition, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, it could also belong to the computation and language sub-category.
3. cs.SD (Sound): Although the paper focuses on visual speech recognition, it could also be relevant to the sound sub-category, as lipreading involves interpreting audio-visual cues.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep learning architecture, which falls under the machine learning sub-category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with processing video data, which is a multimedia task. Therefore, it could also belong to the multimedia sub-category.
